This paper proposes a framework for learning interpretable data representation using LSTM recurrent neural networks over hierarchal graph structures. The paper focuses on the application of semantic object parsing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed method involves the use of LSTM networks, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a novel approach for evolving graph structures, which can be relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
